ArcticDownloader 0.1.9 update log

Purpose:
- Track code changes made in the Linux workspace so they can be mirrored in the Windows workspace.

Format:
- Date
- Change summary
- Files changed
- Notes

Entries:
- 2026-03-17
  - Fixed the Linux Intel XPU readiness check so it validates actual render-node access and no longer depends only on Linux group-name heuristics.
  - Files changed:
    - Cargo.toml
    - src-tauri/Cargo.toml
    - src-tauri/src/main.rs
    - CHANGELOG_0.1.9.md
    - version0.1.9_updates
  - Notes:
    - The Intel XPU status check now inspects `/dev/dri/renderD*` access directly and uses current-session group detection more robustly.
    - This should stop false "log out/login or reboot" warnings on Linux Intel systems where render access is already available.
